data.content:
The arguments are indeed swapped. In MSTest, `Assert.AreEqual` expects **(expected, actual)** — but your code passes `(actual, expected)`. This matters because failure messages will say things like *"Expected: \<result\> but was: \<5\>"*, which is confusing.

**Fix:**

```csharp
// Before (wrong order)
Assert.AreEqual(result, 5);
Assert.AreEqual(result, 0);

// After (correct order: expected, actual)
Assert.AreEqual(5, result);
Assert.AreEqual(0, result);
```

